gerald Kennedy (1917–63) came to North America as immigrants from Ireland in the 1840s. His paternal great-grandparents were Patrick Kennedy (1823–58), born in Dunganstown, County Wexford, Ireland, and Bridget Murphy, who was born probably in Owenduff, County Wexford, Ireland <i>c.</i> 1827; they came to Boston, MA, in 1849. His maternal great-grandparents were Thomas Fitzgerald (1823–85), who was born in Bruff, County Limerick, Ireland, and Rose Anna Cox, who was born probably in Tomregan or Kinawley, County Cavan, Ireland, <i>c.</i> 1835; they came to Boston, MA, in 1857. — An early Scottish Kennedy forebear of a quite different family was British colonial official Archibald Kennedy (1685–1763), the son of Alexander Kennedy of Craigoch, who emigrated to NY <i>c.</i> 1710."],"variants":[{"name":"Canada","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canaday   and   Canida  .","Spanish (<b>Cañada</b>): topographic name from <i>cañada</i> ‘glen, valley’."]},{"name":"Cannady","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canady  ,   Cannaday  , and   Kannady  ."]},{"name":"Cannaday","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canaday  ."]},{"name":"Canedy","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Cannedy  ."]},{"name":"Cannedy","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canedy  ."]},{"name":"Canaday","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canada   and   Cannaday  ."]},{"name":"Canady","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canada  ,   Canaday  , and   Kanady  ."]},{"name":"Canida","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  ."]},{"name":"Kanady","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Canady  ."]},{"name":"Kannady","meanings":["Altered form of Irish and Scottish   Kennedy  . Compare   Cannady   and   Kanady  ."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When John Kennedy 2nd of Blairquhan was born about 1420, in Blairquhan, Ayrshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, John Kennedy 1st of Blairquhan, was 40 and his mother, Mrs John Kennedy I, was 14. He had at least 1 son with Mrs John Kennedy. He died before 12 June 1471."},"et":{"Abt 1420–before 12 June 1471":"umbes 1420–enne 12. juunit 1471","1420–1471":"1420–1471","1425–Female":"1425–Surnud","1440–1500":"1440–1500","1382–1473":"1382–1473","1408–Female":"1408–Surnud","1425":"1425","1500":"1500","Abt 1420":"umbes 1420","before 12 June 1471":"enne 12. juunit 1471","before 1440":"enne 1440","1420":"1420","1473":"1473","1440":"1440","1471":"1471","1382":"1382","1408":"1408","Scotland":"Scotland","Blairquhan, Ayr, Scotland":"Blairquhan, Ayrshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"Abt 1420–before 12 June 1471":"noin 1420–ennen vuotta 12. kesäkuuta 1471","1420–1471":"1420–1471","1425–Female":"1425–Kuollut","1440–1500":"1440–1500","1382–1473":"1382–1473","1408–Female":"1408–Kuollut","1425":"1425","1500":"1500","Abt 1420":"noin 1420","before 12 June 1471":"ennen vuotta 12. kesäkuuta 1471","before 1440":"ennen vuotta 1440","1420":"1420","1473":"1473","1440":"1440","1471":"1471","1382":"1382","1408":"1408","Scotland":"Scotland","Blairquhan, Ayr, Scotland":"Blairquhan, Ayrshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"Abt 1420–before 12 June 1471":"environ 1420–avant 12 juin 1471","1420–1471":"1420–1471","1425–Female":"1425–Décédée","1440–1500":"1440–1500","1382–1473":"1382–1473","1408–Female":"1408–Décédée","1425":"1425","1500":"1500","Abt 1420":"environ 1420","before 12 June 1471":"avant 12 juin 1471","before 1440":"avant 1440","1420":"1420","1473":"1473","1440":"1440","1471":"1471","1382":"1382","1408":"1408","Scotland":"Écosse","Blairquhan, Ayr, Scotland":"Blairquhan, Ayrshire, Écosse, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque John Ke